            "description": "Cryptocurrencies and stocks reacted differently to weak jobs data. Prices at 10:30 p.m. ET: Bitcoin -0.22% at $111,246.07, Ethereum -2.66% at $4,321.10, XRP -1.10% at $2.80, Solana -2.46% at $203.17, Dogecoin -1.52% at $0.2146. Bitcoin hit a low of $109,347.23 before recovering to mid-$111,00s with 11% higher trading volume. Ethereum struggled to rise above $4,300. XRP dropped 1.10%. Bitcoin and Ethereum ETFs saw outflows of $362.31 million and $316.21 million, respectively. $290 million liquidated, with $223 million lost by long-position traders. Bitcoin open interest fell 1.25%. The Puell Multiple indicated a neutral market valuation.",
